body:
Hi,

I would like to make a feature request relating to SystemVerilog assertion support in Yosys. It would be great to have support for named assertions. This is particularly useful when dealing with multiple assertions and when a single property needs to be selected for verification (example: check the following simple example). 

```
module counter(clk, en);
	input clk;
	input en;
	reg [3:0] X;
	initial begin
		X = 4'd1;
	end
	always @(posedge clk) begin
		X <= en ? ( (X == 4'd15) ? 4'd1 : (X + 4'd1) ) : X ;
	end
	property1: assert property ( X != 4'd0 );
	property2: assert property ( X > 4'd0 );
endmodule
```

Based on the name given to an assertion (if any), it looks quite straightforward to add an attribute named \NAME to an assert cell. I would have done this myself, however I am a very new to bison and lexer programming, and wasn't able to make much progress. I would really appreciate if this support could be added.

I am using Yosys as the frontend for the tool I am developing ([here](https://github.com/aman-goel/avr)) which performs word-level property verification.

Please let me know if any detail is required from my side.

Thanks.

--
Aman Goel

